{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1973 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Faridpur Sadar Upazila|Faridpur]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.barc.gov.bd/ Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council''' is the body in charge of the National Agricultural Research System and is located in [[Farmgate]], [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="sad">{{cite web|last1=Islam|first1=Md. Shahidul|title=Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh_Agricultural_Research_Council|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=125 highest taxpayers to get national tax cards|url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/economy/news/127261/125-highest-taxpayers-to-get-national-tax-cards|website=en.prothom-alo.com|publisher=Prothom Alo|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Experts for effective use of vacant land to produce fruits, vegetables|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/10/20/50105/Experts-for-effective-use-of-vacant-land-to-produce-fruits,-vegetables|website=thefinancialexpress-bd.com|publisher=The Financial Express Online Version|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref>
==History== It was established in 1973 by Presidential Order 32. There are currently ten national research institute under the body. Six of the research institute, [[Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute]], [[Soil Resources Development Institute]], [[Bangladesh Jute Research Institute]], [[Bangladesh Institute of Nuclear Agriculture]], [[Bangladesh Rice Research Institute]], and [[Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute]], are [[Ministry of Agriculture (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Agriculture]]. Two research institute are [[Bangladesh Fisheries Research Institute]] and [[Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute]] under [[Ministry of Fisheries and Livestock]]. The [[Bangladesh Tea Research Institute]] under the [[Ministry of Industries (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Industries]]. The [[Bangladesh Forest Research Institute]] under the [[Ministry of Environment and Forest (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Environment and Forest]].<ref name="sad"></ref>
