{{Infobox university |image = |logo = |name = Instituto Nacional de Telecomunicações |motto = ''Construir para a Engenharia Humana'' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]) |mottoeng = Train Humanity in Engineering |established = 1965 |type = |former_names = |endowment = |city = [[Santa Rita do Sapucaí]] |province = [[Minas Gerais]] |country = [[Brazil]] |coor = {{Coord|22|15|26|S|45|41|46|W|region:BR-MG_type:edu|display=inline,title}} |faculty = |staff = |president = Marcelo de Oliveira Marques |undergrad = |postgrad = |campus = [[Urban area|Urban]], 75,000&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup> |colours = |athletics = |nickname = |affiliations = |website = http://www.inatel.br }}
'''Inatel''' is short for '''Instituto Nacional de Telecomunicações''', the National Institute of Communications of [[Brazil]]. The Institute is located on a 75,000&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup> campus in [[Santa Rita do Sapucaí]] in southern [[Minas Gerais]]. Founded in 1965, it specializes in [[Electrical engineering|Electrical Engineering]] and [[Telecommunication]]s education and research.
As of 2007, Inatel's monthly tuition was 950 [[Brazilian real|reais]], and about 5,000 students had graduated from the school.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.brazzil.com/component/content/article/176-february-2007/9820.html|title=How Education and Hard Work Built Up Brazil's Silicon Valley|accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>
The Institute sponsors the biennial '''International Workshop on Telecommunications''' held in odd-numbered years in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bg.ac.rs/eng/en_newss.php?id=62|title=University of Belgrade > News > IWT - International Workshop on Telecommunications|accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>
Researchers at Inatel publish and review technical papers for international conferences.<ref>{{Cite book | editor-last = de Souza | editor-first = José Neuman | others = Petre Dini and Pascal Lorenz | title = Telecommunications and Networking—ICT 2004 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=8Dm7ct1BS7wC&lpg=PR8&ots=gdAK8wR-CV&dq=Inatel%20Brazil&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=false | accessdate = October 26, 2010 | year = 2004 | publisher = Springer Science+Business Media | location = Berlin | isbn = 978-3-540-22571-3 | pages = viii, 82, 312 }}</ref>
