{{italic title}} The '''''Lexicon Iconographicum Mythologiae Classicae''''' (abbreviated '''''LIMC''''') is a multivolume encyclopedia cataloguing representations of [[classical mythology|mythology]] in the [[plastic arts]] of [[classical antiquity]].<ref>Pura Nieto Hernández, ''Mythology: Oxford Bibliographies Online Research Guide'' (Oxford University Press, 2010), p. 45.</ref> Published serially from 1981 to 2009,<ref>[http://www.limc-france.fr LIMC-France.] : database (Ancient objects)</ref> it is the most extensive resource of its kind,<ref>William Hansen, ''Classical Mythology: A Guide to the Mythical World of the Greeks and Romans'' (Oxford University Press, 2004), p. 344.</ref> providing "full and detailed information."<ref>Robin Hard, ''The Routledge Handbook of Greek Mythology'' (Routledge, 2004), p. 691.</ref> Entries are arranged alphabetically, with black-and-white illustrations indexed to their respective entries.<ref>Hansen, ''Classical Mythology'', p. 344</ref>
The work was prepared by international scholars from nearly 40 countries<ref>Boyd Collins ''et al.,'' ''Building a Scholarly Communications Center: Modeling the Rutgers Experience'' (American Library Association, 1999), p. 73.</ref> who contributed in their language of choice, resulting in entries written variously in [[English language|English]], [[German language|German]], [[French language|French]], or [[Italian language|Italian]].<ref>Hansen, ''Classical Mythology'', p. 344.</ref> LIMC also offers a multilingual online database that is updated independently of the print publication.<ref>"Presentation of the databases," [http://www.limc-france.fr/bases LIMC]</ref>
''LIMC'' has been called an "indispensable research instrument,"<ref>Hernandez, ''Mythology'', p. 45.</ref> "monumental,"<ref>Hansen, ''Classical Mythology'', p. 14.</ref> and "magnificent."<ref>Hard, ''Routledge Handbook'', p. 691.</ref>
In the [[United States of America|United States]], ''LIMC'' is based at the [[Rutgers University Libraries|Alexander Library of Rutgers University]].<ref>Collins ''et al.,'' ''Building a Scholarly Communications Center'', p. 73.</ref>
== Volumes == * ''Lexicon Iconographicum Mythologiae Classicae'' (''LIMC''), Artemis & Winkler Verlag (Zürich, München, Düsseldorf), 1981-1999 {{ISBN|3-7608-8751-1}} :Vol. I: Aara - Aphlad (1981) :Vol. II: Aphrodisias - Athena (1984) :Vol. III: Atherion - Eros / Amor, Cupido (1986) :Vol. IV: Eros (in Etruria) - Herakles (1988) :Vol. V: Herakles - Kenchrias (1990) :Vol. VI: Kentauroi et Kentaurides - Oiax (1992) :Vol. VII: Oidipous - Theseus (1994) :Vol. VIII: Thespiades - Zodiacus et Supplementum (1997) :Indices ::1. Museums, Collections, Sites (1999) ::2. Literary and Epigraphical Sources mentioning lost Works. Mythological Names (1999)
* ''Lexicon Iconographicum Mythologiae Classicae. Supplementum 2009'' (''LIMC''), Artemis Verlag (Düsseldorf), 2009. {{ISBN|978-3-538-03520-1}}
